OL,7,FAllegations that he told a pupil to
OL,8,Fchange an exam answer and/or told the
OL,9,Fsame pupil to change an exam answer
OL,10,Ffrom the correct answer to an
OL,11,Fincorrect answer were found not proved.
OL,13,FOn the final day of the remote hearing
OL,14,Fon December 9, the panel concluded
OL,15,Fthat the allegations found proved
OL,16,Fagainst Trigg-Turner showed he had
OL,17,Flacked integrity and honesty on those
OL,18,Fmatters and that taken together, or
OL,19,Fseparately, they amounted to
OL,20,Funacceptable professional conduct.
