OL,7,FWeighed against this, the school
OL,8,Fshould have acted sooner, she said.
OL,10,FMs Beard-Robbins added: "At no point
OL,11,Fwas there formal management discussion
OL,12,Fin the school (about the reports made
OL,13,Ffrom colleagues regarding Trigg-
OL,14,FTurner). The committee think this
OL,15,Fwould have been appropriate. Had
OL,16,Fformal discussion taken place Mr Trigg-
OL,17,FTurner might have had the opportunity
OL,18,Fto reflect and change his conduct."
